caption: Little Joe's  has the best deep dish Pizza in the city! If you go there and don't order the deep dish you were mis-informed about what to eat. Good to order and take home, or eat there. The atmosphere is a little off inside the restaurant...the tables aren't set up to match the unique art and paint on the wall, they could have a better set up...BUT the pizza more than makes up for it! Who cares how you sit when the food is that GOOD!

If you teach at UFC or in the Taylor Street area this is your after work hang out. Cold beer, hard liquor, fair prices, good service from the bar.

This is your typical neighborhood dive, in a part of town with a large student population. The drinks are relatively cheap and it is small, but it is a good watering hole. There isn't a kitchen in-house, but there are options close by to get food and they allow you to bring that in. There is a jukebox and the bartenders are cool as well, and is a solid watering hole for anyone looking to tie one on in the area

It's truly amazing that this place is still open. I think they have 4 taps, all of them pouring PBR (while one of the PBR taps tastes like Malort). This place used to have the best bartenders this city ever had to offer. Back four to five years ago, I couldn't wait to go to little joes. It was NOT a good night unless I went to Little Joes. But this seems to have ended. None of the cool bartenders are there, just snarky frat boys, mean old men, and jag offs behind the counter that are never able to pour you one.

Great local option for college students looking for inexpensive options to fill up the tank on PBR and Long Island ice teas. The bouncer Andy was on point with security, patting me down thoroughly and paying extra attention to my inner thighs, which is where terrorists usually hide their dangerous club-like femur bones. I appreciate his dedication to safety in this post 9-11 world. As long as we make it a point to go to Little Joe's on $5 PBR pitcher night and try to impress sorority girls with our extra small Hollister shirts and Axe body spray, ISIS will never win.

The best neighborhood bar around!  Any chance our friends have to get together for a chill-- but always fun -- night, we head here. Just come to enjoy the "home-y" feel and have beer, you might fall in love with it just as we did!
